Bambu Printer LAN
========

Bambu Printer LAN is a derivative work and re-implementation that reuses and is based on:

- BambuStudio  — Copyright (C) Bambu Lab — AGPL-3.0
  https://github.com/bambulab/BambuStudio
- PrusaSlicer  — Copyright (C) Prusa Research — AGPL-3.0
  https://github.com/prusa3d/PrusaSlicer
- Slic3r       — Copyright (C) Alessandro Ranellucci and contributors — AGPL-3.0
  https://github.com/Slic3r/Slic3r

The C++ slicing engine (libslic3r and bundled libraries) is reused from the
above projects under the AGPL-3.0 and remains under that license.

The Bambu Lab networking plugin (closed-source) is NOT included or
redistributed. The networking layer in this project (`:net:bambu` and
`relay/`) is an independent clean-room re-implementation based on observed
protocol behavior and public community documentation.

Third-party Android/Kotlin and Python dependencies are listed in
gradle/libs.versions.toml and relay/requirements.txt with their own licenses.
